div.font: The mechanical output of the DC motor changes depending on the direction it is driven.

In one direction, the pre-feeder drive is engaged, pushing the filament to the main feed-drive. In the other direction, the gear arm swings to drive the re-spooling wheel, which engages with the filament spool edge.
The swing-arm is also a one-way ratchet, so the filament can be pulled thru the pre-feededer by the main feed drive once the filament has reached it.
